          "name": "Oldest Manhole Cover",
          "description": "The manhole cover on Jersey street is New York’s oldest manhole cover and used to allow access to the Croton Aqueduct, built in the early 1840s.Although the aqueduct was drained to create the Great Lawn in Central Park, this tiny manhole in SoHo is a lasting tribute to the infrastructure that supported a growing metropolis from the days of horse and buggy travel.Update March 2018: Sadly, the city of New York has replaced this manhole cover.  If you enter Central Park on at 85th Street on the west side and take the smaller path to the left, they're about 70 steps in.Sign up for our newsletter and get the best of Atlas Obscura in your inbox.",
