          "name": "Nicholas Roerich Museum",
          "description": "Marvelous little townhouse museum dedicated the incredible life and visionary art of Russian mystic Nicholas Roerich (Никола́й Константи́нович Ре́рих), who in the 1920s explored Himalayan Asia “from Sikkim through Punjab, Kashmir, Ladakh, the Karakoram Mountains, Khotan, Kashgar, Qara Shar, Urumchi, Irtysh, the Altai Mountains, the Oryot region of Mongolia, the Central Gobi, Kansu, Tsaidam, and Tibet.”#1 Subway to 103 Street, walk north on Broadway to 107th Street, turn left and walk past West End Avenue, almost to Riverside Drive. Last townhouse on the north side of street, right before massive white mansion. Don't bother asking locals for directions - I swear, nobody knows about this place.Sign up for our newsletter and get the best of Atlas Obscura in your inbox.",
