          "name": "Manhatta",
          "image": "https://media.timeout.com/images/105263849/630/472/image.jpg",
          "cuisine": "Contemporary American",
          "cost": 3,
          "description": "Manhatta sits 60 floors up in a FiDi skyscraper with a name borrowed from Walt Whitman’s love poem to the city, which guests will be immediately understand thanks to the sweeping views from the 360-degree floor-to-ceiling windows. Diners of the 90-seat restaurant will enjoy the best views in town while chowing down on chef Jason Pfeifer's (Maialino, Per Se) New American dishes, like peekytoe crab with poached leeks and crispy artichokes or wagyu bavette with pommes anna and Harbison cheese.",
          "why_go": "Why Go? The views plus a price tag of $78 for three courses essentially makes it a steal",
