          "cuisine": "Contemporary American",
          "cost": 3,
          "description": "From the moment it opened, Andrew Carmellini’s rollicking Soho eatery seemed destined to join the ranks of neighborhood classics like Balthazar and Blue Ribbon. The virtuoso chef offers diners an exuberant gastro-tour of the American melting pot, making stops in the barrio, New England and even the Mexican border. ",
